{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":700,"text":"The problem I want to talk with you\nabout is really the problem of:"},{"time":5700,"text":"How does one supply health care\nin a world in which cost is everything?"},{"time":13014,"text":"How do you do that?"},{"time":15199,"text":"And the basic paradigm\nwe want to suggest to you,"},{"time":17558,"text":"I want to suggest to you,"},{"time":18807,"text":"is one in which you say\nthat in order to treat disease,"},{"time":22503,"text":"you have to first know\nwhat you're treating, that's diagnostics,"},{"time":25899,"text":"and then you have to do something."}]},{"cues":[{"time":27570,"text":"The program we're involved in is something\nwe call \"Diagnostics for All,\""},{"time":31910,"text":"or \"zero-cost diagnostics.\""},{"time":34045,"text":"How do you provide medically\nrelevant information"},{"time":37483,"text":"at as close as possible to zero cost?"},{"time":40131,"text":"How do you do it?"},{"time":41385,"text":"Let me just give you two examples."},{"time":43707,"text":"The rigors of military medicine are not\nso dissimilar from the third world:"},{"time":49597,"text":"poor resources, a rigorous environment --\na series of problems --"},{"time":53973,"text":"light weight and things of this kind."},{"time":55978,"text":"And also they're not so different\nfrom the home health care"},{"time":59436,"text":"and diagnostic system world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":61865,"text":"So, the technology I want to talk\nabout is for the third world,"},{"time":66737,"text":"for the developing world,"},{"time":68159,"text":"but it has, I think,\nmuch broader application,"},{"time":70724,"text":"because information is so important\nin the health care system."},{"time":75041,"text":"So you see two examples here."},{"time":76859,"text":"One is a lab that is actually\na fairly high-end laboratory in Africa."},{"time":82632,"text":"The second is basically an entrepreneur\nwho is set up and doing who-knows-what"},{"time":86960,"text":"at a table in a market."},{"time":88431,"text":"I don't know what kind\nof health care is delivered there."},{"time":91402,"text":"But it's not really\nwhat is probably most efficient."}]},{"cues":[{"time":96341,"text":"What is our approach?"},{"time":99442,"text":"The way in which one typically\napproaches a problem of lowering cost,"},{"time":104991,"text":"starting from the perspective\nof the United States,"},{"time":107878,"text":"is to take our solution,"},{"time":110045,"text":"and then try to cut cost out of it."},{"time":112763,"text":"No matter how you do that,"},{"time":114200,"text":"you're not going to start\nwith a $100,000 instrument"},{"time":116730,"text":"and bring it down to no cost."},{"time":118175,"text":"It isn't going to work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":119372,"text":"So the approach we took\nwas the other way around, to ask:"},{"time":122255,"text":"What is the cheapest possible stuff"},{"time":124744,"text":"that you could make\na diagnostic system out of,"},{"time":127704,"text":"and get useful information\nand add function?"},{"time":130275,"text":"And what we've chosen is paper."},{"time":132296,"text":"What you see here is a prototypic device."},{"time":135344,"text":"It's about a centimeter on the side."},{"time":137200,"text":"It's about the size of a fingernail."},{"time":139201,"text":"The lines around the edges are a polymer."},{"time":142828,"text":"It's made of paper."},{"time":144694,"text":"And paper, of course, wicks fluid,\nas you know, paper, cloth --"},{"time":149403,"text":"drop wine on the tablecloth,"},{"time":151303,"text":"and the wine wicks all over everything."},{"time":154064,"text":"Put it on your shirt, it ruins the shirt."},{"time":156127,"text":"That's what a hydrophilic surface does."}]},{"cues":[{"time":158890,"text":"So in this device, the idea\nis that you drip the bottom end of it"},{"time":162537,"text":"in a drop of, in this case, urine."},{"time":165200,"text":"The fluid wicks its way\ninto those chambers at the top."},{"time":168972,"text":"The brown color indicates\nthe amount of glucose in the urine,"},{"time":173200,"text":"the blue color indicates the amount\nof protein in the urine."},{"time":176771,"text":"And the combination of those two\nis a first-order shot"},{"time":179831,"text":"at a number of useful things\nthat you want."},{"time":182977,"text":"So, this is an example of a device\nmade from a simple piece of paper."}]},{"cues":[{"time":186358,"text":"Now, how simple can you make\nthe production?"},{"time":189200,"text":"Why do we choose paper?"},{"time":191459,"text":"There's an example\nof the same thing on a finger,"},{"time":194393,"text":"showing you basically what it looks like."},{"time":196673,"text":"One reason for using paper\nis that it's everywhere."},{"time":199125,"text":"We have made these kinds of devices\nusing napkins and toilet paper"},{"time":204322,"text":"and wraps, and all kinds of stuff."}]},{"cues":[{"time":206576,"text":"So the production capability is there."},{"time":209038,"text":"The second is, you can put lots and lots\nof tests in a very small place."},{"time":213359,"text":"I'll show you in a moment\nthat the stack of paper there"},{"time":216202,"text":"would probably hold\nsomething like 100,000 tests,"},{"time":218958,"text":"something of that kind."}]},{"cues":[{"time":220723,"text":"And then finally, a point\nyou don't think of so much"},{"time":223592,"text":"in developed world medicine:"},{"time":226200,"text":"it eliminates sharps."},{"time":227903,"text":"And what sharps means\nis needles, things that stick."},{"time":231309,"text":"If you've taken a sample\nof someone's blood"},{"time":233627,"text":"and the someone might have hepatitis C,"},{"time":236148,"text":"you don't want to make a mistake\nand stick it in you."},{"time":238719,"text":"You don't want to do that."},{"time":240040,"text":"So how do you dispose of that?"},{"time":241553,"text":"It's a problem everywhere,\nand here, you simply burn it."},{"time":244259,"text":"So it's a sort of a practical approach\nto starting on things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":249417,"text":"Now, you say, \"If paper is a good idea,"},{"time":253097,"text":"other people have surely thought of it.\""},{"time":255084,"text":"And the answer is, of course, yes."},{"time":256990,"text":"Those half of you, roughly, who are women,"},{"time":260834,"text":"at some point may have had\na pregnancy test."},{"time":263320,"text":"And the most common of these\nis in a device"},{"time":267328,"text":"that looks like the thing on the left."},{"time":269200,"text":"It's something called\na lateral-flow immunoassay."},{"time":271716,"text":"In that particular test,"},{"time":273200,"text":"urine, either containing\na hormone called hCG,"},{"time":276839,"text":"does or does not flow\nacross a piece of paper."},{"time":280200,"text":"And there are two bars; one bar\nindicates that the test is working,"},{"time":284125,"text":"and if the second bar shows up,\nyou're pregnant."}]},{"cues":[{"time":287314,"text":"This is a terrific kind of test\nin a binary world,"},{"time":290509,"text":"and the nice thing about pregnancy\nis either you are pregnant"},{"time":293448,"text":"or you're not pregnant;"},{"time":294626,"text":"you're not partially pregnant\nor thinking about being pregnant"},{"time":297631,"text":"or something of that sort."},{"time":298939,"text":"So it works very well there,\nbut it doesn't work very well"},{"time":301698,"text":"when you need more\nquantitative information."}]},{"cues":[{"time":303808,"text":"There are also dipsticks,"},{"time":305052,"text":"but if you look at the dipsticks,"},{"time":306822,"text":"they're for another kind\nof urine analysis."},{"time":309059,"text":"There are an awful lot of colors\nand things like that."},{"time":311960,"text":"What do you actually do about that\nin a difficult circumstance?"},{"time":316372,"text":"So the approach we started with is to ask:"},{"time":320705,"text":"Is it really practical\nto make things of this sort?"},{"time":324200,"text":"And that problem is now,\nin a purely engineering way, solved."},{"time":328511,"text":"And the procedure that we have\nis simply to start with paper."},{"time":332084,"text":"You run it through a new kind\nof printer called a wax printer."},{"time":335654,"text":"The wax printer does\nwhat looks like printing."},{"time":338310,"text":"It is printing."},{"time":339492,"text":"You put that on, you warm it a little bit,"},{"time":341556,"text":"the wax prints through,\nso it absorbs into the paper,"},{"time":344623,"text":"and you end up with the device you want."}]},{"cues":[{"time":346791,"text":"The printers cost 800 bucks now."},{"time":349894,"text":"We estimate that if you were\nto run them 24 hours a day,"},{"time":353806,"text":"they'd make about 10 million tests a year."},{"time":355938,"text":"So it's a solved problem.\nThat particular problem is solved."},{"time":359186,"text":"And there is an example\nof the kind of thing that you see."},{"time":361986,"text":"That's on a piece of 8 by 12 paper."},{"time":363849,"text":"That takes about two seconds to make."},{"time":366142,"text":"And so I regard that as done."},{"time":368808,"text":"There's a very important issue here,"},{"time":370626,"text":"which is that because it's a printer,\na color printer, it prints colors."},{"time":375068,"text":"That's what color printers do."},{"time":376616,"text":"I'll show you in a moment,\nthat's actually quite useful."}]},{"cues":[{"time":380651,"text":"Now, the next question\nthat you would like to ask is:"},{"time":383200,"text":"What would you like to measure?\nWhat would you like to analyze?"},{"time":386415,"text":"And the thing you'd most like to analyze,\nwe're a fair distance from."},{"time":391200,"text":"It's what's called\n\"fever of undiagnosed origin.\""},{"time":395200,"text":"Someone comes into the clinic,\nthey have a fever, they feel bad."},{"time":398785,"text":"What do they have?"},{"time":399975,"text":"Do they have TB? Do they have AIDS?\nDo they have a common cold?"},{"time":403401,"text":"The triage problem."},{"time":404639,"text":"That's a hard problem for reasons\nI won't go through."},{"time":407319,"text":"There are an awful lot of things\nthat you'd like to distinguish among."},{"time":410885,"text":"But then there are a series of things --"},{"time":413111,"text":"AIDS, hepatitis, malaria, TB, others --"},{"time":416719,"text":"and simpler ones,\nsuch as guidance of treatment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":420238,"text":"Now, even that's more\ncomplicated than you think."},{"time":423200,"text":"A friend of mine works\nin transcultural psychiatry,"},{"time":427439,"text":"and he is interested in the question"},{"time":429569,"text":"of why people do\nand don't take their meds."},{"time":432323,"text":"So Dapsone, or something like that,\nyou have to take for a while."},{"time":435922,"text":"He has a wonderful story\nof talking to a villager in India"},{"time":439562,"text":"and saying,"},{"time":440737,"text":"\"Have you taken your Dapsone?\" \"Yes.\""},{"time":442567,"text":"\"Have you taken it every day?\" \"Yes.\""},{"time":444457,"text":"\"Have you taken if for a month?\" \"Yes.\""},{"time":446435,"text":"What the guy actually meant"},{"time":447960,"text":"was that he'd fed a 30-day dose of Dapsone\nto his dog that morning."}]},{"cues":[{"time":451886,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":453035,"text":"And he was telling the truth,\nbecause in a different culture,"},{"time":456815,"text":"the dog is a surrogate for you;"},{"time":459413,"text":"\"today,\" \"this month,\"\n\"since the rainy season\" --"},{"time":462580,"text":"there are lots of opportunities\nfor misunderstanding."}]},{"cues":[{"time":465088,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":466119,"text":"And so an issue here is to,\nin some cases, figure out"},{"time":469707,"text":"how to deal with matters\nthat seem uninteresting, like compliance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":475160,"text":"Now, take a look\nat what a typical test looks like."},{"time":479419,"text":"Prick a finger, you get some blood --\nabout 50 microliters."},{"time":483200,"text":"That's about all you're going to get,"},{"time":485055,"text":"because you can't use\nthe usual sort of systems."},{"time":489585,"text":"You can't manipulate it very well;"},{"time":491283,"text":"I'll show something\nabout that in a moment."},{"time":493423,"text":"So you take the drop of blood,\nno further manipulations,"},{"time":496200,"text":"you put it on a little device,"},{"time":498007,"text":"the device filters out the blood cells,\nlets the serum go through,"},{"time":502704,"text":"and you get a series of colors\ndown in the bottom there."},{"time":506489,"text":"And the colors indicate\n\"disease\" or \"normal.\""},{"time":510672,"text":"But even that's complicated,"},{"time":512378,"text":"because to me, colors\nmight indicate \"normal,\""},{"time":516003,"text":"but after all, we're all suffering\nfrom probably an excess of education."}]},{"cues":[{"time":520987,"text":"What do you do about something\nwhich requires quantitative analysis?"},{"time":525598,"text":"And so the solution\nthat we and many other people"},{"time":528304,"text":"are thinking about there,"},{"time":529939,"text":"and at this point,\nthere is a dramatic flourish,"},{"time":532552,"text":"and out comes the universal solution\nto everything these days,"},{"time":535748,"text":"which is a cell phone --"},{"time":536929,"text":"in this particular case, a camera phone."},{"time":538951,"text":"They're everywhere --\nsix billion a month in India."},{"time":543200,"text":"And the idea is that what one does\nis to take the device,"},{"time":548746,"text":"you dip it, you develop the color,"},{"time":551200,"text":"you take a picture,\nthe picture goes to a central laboratory."},{"time":554449,"text":"You don't have to send out a doctor,"},{"time":556200,"text":"you send out somebody\nwho can just take the sample,"},{"time":558965,"text":"and in the clinic either a doctor,\nor ideally, a computer in this case,"},{"time":562714,"text":"does the analysis."},{"time":563902,"text":"Turns out to work actually quite well,"},{"time":565777,"text":"particularly when your color printer\nhas printed the color bars"},{"time":568893,"text":"that indicate how things work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":570738,"text":"So my view of the health care\nworker of the future"},{"time":573786,"text":"is not a doctor, but an 18-year-old,"},{"time":576377,"text":"otherwise unemployed, who has two things:"},{"time":579153,"text":"a backpack full\nof these tests and a lancet"},{"time":581260,"text":"to occasionally take a blood sample,"},{"time":583200,"text":"and an AK-47."},{"time":584783,"text":"And these are the things\nthat get him through his day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":587403,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":590112,"text":"There's another very\ninteresting connection here,"},{"time":592471,"text":"and that is, that what one wants to do\nis pass through useful information"},{"time":598035,"text":"over what is generally\na pretty awful telephone system."},{"time":601590,"text":"It turns out there's an enormous\namount of information"},{"time":604200,"text":"already available on that subject,\nwhich is the Mars Rover problem."},{"time":607603,"text":"How do you get back an accurate view\nof the color on Mars"},{"time":611494,"text":"if you have a really terrible\nbandwidth to do it with?"},{"time":615304,"text":"And the answer is not complicated,"},{"time":617200,"text":"but it's one which I don't want\nto go through here,"},{"time":619765,"text":"other than to say that the communication\nsystems for doing this"},{"time":622833,"text":"are really pretty well understood."}]},{"cues":[{"time":624558,"text":"Also, a fact which you may not know"},{"time":627319,"text":"is that the compute capability\nof this thing is not so different"},{"time":631077,"text":"from the compute capability\nof your desktop computer."},{"time":633940,"text":"This is a fantastic device\nwhich is only beginning to be tapped."},{"time":637625,"text":"I don't know whether the idea\nof one computer, one child"},{"time":641095,"text":"makes any sense."},{"time":642270,"text":"Here's the computer of the future,"},{"time":644200,"text":"because this screen is already there\nand they're ubiquitous."}]},{"cues":[{"time":648851,"text":"All right, let me show you just\na little bit about advanced devices."},{"time":652112,"text":"And we'll start by posing\na little problem."},{"time":654290,"text":"What you see here\nis another centimeter-sized device,"},{"time":657711,"text":"and the different colors\nare different colors of dye."},{"time":661718,"text":"And you notice something"},{"time":662920,"text":"which might strike you\nas a little bit interesting,"},{"time":665643,"text":"which is, the yellow seems to disappear,"},{"time":668524,"text":"get through the blue,\nand then get through the red."},{"time":671037,"text":"How does that happen?"},{"time":672214,"text":"How do you make something\nflow through something?"},{"time":674813,"text":"And, of course the answer is, \"You don't.\""},{"time":677032,"text":"You make it flow under and over."}]},{"cues":[{"time":678799,"text":"But now the question is:"},{"time":679984,"text":"How do you make it flow\nunder and over in a piece of paper?"},{"time":683550,"text":"The answer is that what you do --"},{"time":686520,"text":"and the details are not\nterribly important here --"},{"time":689200,"text":"is to make something more elaborate:"},{"time":691115,"text":"You take several different\nlayers of paper,"},{"time":693216,"text":"each one containing\nits own little fluid system,"},{"time":696311,"text":"and you separate them by pieces of,\nliterally, double-sided carpet tape,"},{"time":700924,"text":"the stuff you use to stick\nthe carpets onto the floor."},{"time":703834,"text":"And the fluid will flow\nfrom one layer into the next."},{"time":707084,"text":"It distributes itself,\nflows through further holes,"},{"time":710200,"text":"distributes itself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":711813,"text":"And what you see,\nat the lower right-hand side there,"},{"time":715078,"text":"is a sample in which a single sample\nof blood has been put on the top,"},{"time":720401,"text":"and it has gone through\nand distributed itself"},{"time":722935,"text":"into these 16 holes on the bottom,"},{"time":726305,"text":"in a piece of paper --\nbasically, it looks like a chip,"},{"time":729033,"text":"two pieces of paper thick."},{"time":730795,"text":"And in this particular case,"},{"time":732302,"text":"we were just interested\nin the replicability of that."},{"time":735090,"text":"But that is, in principle,\nthe way you solve"},{"time":737418,"text":"the \"fever of unexplained origin\" problem,"},{"time":739598,"text":"because each one of those spots\nthen becomes a test"},{"time":742378,"text":"for a particular set\nof markers of disease,"},{"time":746001,"text":"and this will work in due course."}]},{"cues":[{"time":748291,"text":"Here is an example of a slightly\nmore complicated device."},{"time":751631,"text":"There's the chip."},{"time":752837,"text":"You dip in a corner."},{"time":754077,"text":"The fluid goes into the center."},{"time":755648,"text":"It distributes itself out\ninto these various wells or holes"},{"time":759455,"text":"and turns color,"},{"time":760715,"text":"all done with paper and carpet tape."},{"time":763432,"text":"So it's, I think, as low-cost"},{"time":765613,"text":"as we're likely to be able\nto come up and make things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":769432,"text":"Now, I have two last\nlittle stories to tell you"},{"time":772752,"text":"in finishing off this business."},{"time":775386,"text":"This is one:"},{"time":776575,"text":"One of the things\nyou occasionally need to do"},{"time":779040,"text":"is separate blood cells from serum."},{"time":782874,"text":"And the question was,"},{"time":784583,"text":"here we do it by taking a sample,"},{"time":786708,"text":"we put it in a centrifuge, we spin it,"},{"time":790594,"text":"and you get blood cells out."},{"time":793085,"text":"Terrific."},{"time":794268,"text":"What happens if you don't have\nelectricity, a centrifuge, and whatever?"},{"time":797739,"text":"And we thought for a while\nof how you might do this,"},{"time":800279,"text":"and the way, in fact, you do it,\nis what's shown here."},{"time":802940,"text":"You get an eggbeater, which is everywhere,\nand you saw off a blade,"},{"time":807571,"text":"and then you take tubing,\nand you stick it on that."},{"time":810078,"text":"You put the blood in,\nsomebody sits there and spins it."},{"time":812842,"text":"It works really, really well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":814985,"text":"And we sat down,\nwe did the physics of eggbeaters"},{"time":817423,"text":"and self-aligning tubes\nand all the rest of that kind of thing,"},{"time":820524,"text":"and sent it off to a journal."},{"time":822010,"text":"We were very proud of this,"},{"time":823356,"text":"particularly the title,\nwhich was \"Eggbeater as Centrifuge.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":826242,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":827340,"text":"And we sent it off,"},{"time":828515,"text":"and by return mail, it came back."},{"time":830446,"text":"I called up the editor and I said,"},{"time":832200,"text":"\"What's going on? How is this possible?\""},{"time":834346,"text":"The editor said, with enormous disdain,"},{"time":837504,"text":"\"I read this."},{"time":838971,"text":"And we're not going to publish it,\nbecause we only publish science.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":842751,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":844188,"text":"And it's an important issue,"},{"time":845681,"text":"because it means\nthat we have to, as a society,"},{"time":849103,"text":"think about what we value."},{"time":851104,"text":"And if it's just papers\nand Phys. Rev. letters,"},{"time":853912,"text":"we've got a problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":855818,"text":"Here is another example\nof something which is --"},{"time":859072,"text":"this is a little spectrophotometer."},{"time":861137,"text":"It measures the absorption\nof light in a sample."},{"time":864451,"text":"The neat thing about this is,"},{"time":865954,"text":"you have a light source that flickers\non and off at about 1,000 hertz,"},{"time":869669,"text":"another light source\nthat detects that light at 1,000 hertz,"},{"time":873362,"text":"and so you can run this system\nin broad daylight."},{"time":876200,"text":"It performs about equivalently"},{"time":878293,"text":"to a system that's on the order\nof 100,000 dollars."},{"time":882886,"text":"It costs 50 dollars."},{"time":884071,"text":"We can probably make it for 50 cents\nif we put our mind to it."},{"time":888200,"text":"Why doesn't somebody do it?"},{"time":890097,"text":"The answer is:"},{"time":891272,"text":"How do you make a profit\nin a capitalist system, doing that?"},{"time":894566,"text":"Interesting problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":897315,"text":"So, let me finish by saying\nthat we've thought about this"},{"time":902292,"text":"as a kind of engineering problem."},{"time":904518,"text":"And we've asked: What\nis the scientific unifying idea here?"},{"time":908924,"text":"And we've decided\nwe should think about this"},{"time":911072,"text":"not so much in terms of cost,\nbut in terms of simplicity."},{"time":914200,"text":"Simplicity is a neat word."},{"time":915802,"text":"You've got to think\nabout what simplicity means."},{"time":918755,"text":"I know what it is,"},{"time":919935,"text":"but I don't actually know what it means."}]},{"cues":[{"time":922136,"text":"So I actually was interested\nenough in this"},{"time":924257,"text":"to put together several groups of people."},{"time":928644,"text":"The most recent involved\na couple of people at MIT,"},{"time":931200,"text":"one of them being\nan exceptionally bright kid"},{"time":933344,"text":"who is one of the very\nfew people I would think of"},{"time":936078,"text":"who's an authentic genius."},{"time":937491,"text":"We all struggled for an entire day\nto think about simplicity."},{"time":941565,"text":"And I want to give you the answer\nof this deep scientific thought."}]},{"cues":[{"time":945771,"text":"[What is simplicity?"},{"time":947128,"text":"\"It's impossible to f..k it up\"]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":948739,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":949812,"text":"So, in a sense, you get what you pay for."}]},{"cues":[{"time":952286,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":953819,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}